- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with completeness results for a logical system, specifically Multiplicative Exponential Linear Logic (MELL). 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as MELL is a type of linear logic that has been used in programming language semantics. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may have applications in machine learning theory. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a less likely category, but MELL has been used in the study of complexity classes, so it is a possibility. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the least likely category, but still possible as MELL has been used in the study of data structures and algorithms.
